[b]Update v1.1[/b]

[b]StochRSI — cross signals on the price chart[/b]

K/D crossovers in the overbought or oversold zone are now marked directly on the candlestick chart as small colored dots — green below the candle for bullish crosses, red above for bearish. Dot size scales with Setup Pressure so structurally backed setups stand out visually. Zone thresholds are configurable (default 25 / 75).

[b]StochRSI — divergences[/b]

Bullish and bearish divergences between price pivots and the StochRSI K line are now detected and drawn as lines in the oscillator — the same visual approach as the existing Impulse divergence.

[b]MFI overlay (new)[/b]

The Money Flow Index is now available as an optional thin lavender curve in the oscillator panel (default off). Unlike StochRSI, MFI incorporates volume direction — it measures whether volume is flowing into up moves or down moves. MFI divergences are detected and shown as connecting lines in the oscillator. When price diverges from MFI, a [b]◆[/b] diamond marker appears directly on the price chart. The chart marker is independently toggleable — it can be visible even when the MFI curve is hidden in the oscillator.

[b]Divergence — master toggle[/b]

A single [i]Show Divergences[/i] toggle now controls all divergence sources (Impulse, StochRSI, MFI). Bullish and bearish are still individually toggleable beneath it.

[b]Dashboard — show/hide toggle[/b]

The info table can now be hidden via a dedicated toggle in the new [i]Dashboard[/i] settings group.

[b]Chart markers decoupled from oscillator curves[/b]

StochRSI cross dots and MFI divergence markers on the price chart are independent of whether the corresponding curves are visible in the oscillator pane. Each can be shown or hidden separately.
